on this project,


40:59.352 --> 41:02.855
you can go
and play it months from now.


41:02.855 --> 41:05.900
You might face some
discouraging circumstance.


41:05.900 --> 41:09.320
Well, go back,
and you can stop it


41:09.320 --> 41:11.322
—think about it.


41:11.322 --> 41:14.617
I mean, what a blessing,
especially for you graduates


41:14.617 --> 41:17.954
to be able to go back
and then just absorb more.


41:17.953 --> 41:22.958
So keep that in mind,
and Jehovah will bless you


41:22.958 --> 41:27.880
with good, good reminders
in the days ahead.


41:27.880 --> 41:31.300
So at this point,
we’re going to invite all—


41:31.300 --> 41:36.263
Now, we were supposed
to all be ready to sing this new song,


41:36.263 --> 41:39.516
and I know
my wife and I practiced.


41:39.517 --> 41:41.519
We hope you practiced.


41:41.518 --> 41:44.480
Those that know
how to read music,


41:44.480 --> 41:48.693
please sing out
and help those around you.


41:48.693 --> 41:52.613
It’s a beautiful song,
and I love the lyrics now.


41:52.613 --> 41:54.365
See, because we’ve had—


41:54.365 --> 41:59.162
One of my favorites is song 135
in the songbook we have at this point.


41:59.162 --> 42:01.749
But see,
this has a message here,


42:01.748 --> 42:05.168
and you sing and you keep
this in mind in your assignment:


42:05.168 --> 42:08.463
“We Will,” not might,


42:08.463 --> 42:10.881
“We Will Keep Enduring.”


42:10.882 --> 42:14.802
So take these lyrics to heart
as you go to your assignments.


42:14.802 --> 42:17.555
So let’s stand
and sing song number 154.


42:17.555 --> 42:19.390
And then Brother Leon Weaver,


42:19.390 --> 42:21.683
a helper to the Service Committee
of the Governing Body,


42:21.683 --> 46:06.305
will conclude with prayer.

